 also functions as the capital of the Canton of Bern, the second most populous of Switzerland's cantons.
</PARAGRAPH>

<PARAGRAPH>
Illustrious Bernese include the reformer Albrecht von Haller, the poet Albert Bitzius and the painters Hans Fries, Ferdinand Hodler and Paul Klee. The German-born physicist Albert Einstein worked out his theory of relativity while employed as a clerk at the Bern patent office.
A culturally important person was Mani Matter, a songwriter performing in Bernese German.</PARAGRAPH>
